<h1 class="hero-h">AI Consultant San Francisco / Bay Area <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Remote-first AI consulting for Bay Area B2B.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Treetop works with San Francisco and Bay Area B2B companies remotely. We're not the right firm for Bay Area B2B AI consulting in every case — here's an honest take on when we're the right fit and when you should look elsewhere.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Treetop works with Bay Area B2B companies remote-first. We're particularly relevant for B2B SaaS at \$5M-\$30M ARR rolling out Claude or ChatGPT Team. We're not the right firm for very large enterprises or pure AI engineering work — those need different shops.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When Treetop is the right fit for Bay Area B2B</h2><ul class="ul"><li>B2B SaaS at \$5M-\$30M ARR with messy or absent AI rollout.</li><li>Need someone who has shipped real workflows, not just produced strategy decks.</li><li>Want AI rollout that compounds with marketing/sales execution, not just an isolated AI initiative.</li><li>Remote-first works for the engagement (we'll travel for kickoffs and quarterly check-ins, not weekly).</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When you should look elsewhere</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Enterprise (1,000+ people).</strong> Different operating model required; pick a firm specialized in enterprise AI rollout.</li><li><strong>Pure AI engineering or model development.</strong> We do not build foundation models or custom LLMs. Pick an AI engineering shop.</li><li><strong>Need someone on-site full-time.</strong> Remote-first model means we cannot be in your office daily.</li><li><strong>Pre-product-market-fit startups.</strong> AI rollout is not the priority; fix the product.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">How we work with Bay Area clients</h2><ul class="ul"><li>AI Audit (\$1,500) as a low-commitment first engagement — produces a written roadmap.</li><li>Fixed-fee implementation (\$5K-\$50K) for 1-3 production workflows.</li><li>Quarterly on-site visits to SF for major milestones.</li><li>Weekly remote cadence in between.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Bay Area context that shapes our work</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Higher baseline AI fluency in your team than at most clients — adoption curve is faster.</li><li>Existing tool stacks are often more sprawling — audit usually surfaces overlap and waste.</li><li>Buyer expectations on the company's AI usage are higher — having a credible AI story matters for sales.</li><li>Talent market for AI ops roles is competitive — hiring takes longer than other markets.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you have an SF office?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Remote-first. On-site visits to SF for client engagements.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Have you worked with Bay Area B2B SaaS?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — substantial portion of our practice.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you offer on-site presence beyond quarterly?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Negotiable per engagement. Some clients have engaged us for monthly visits; not standard.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What's your AI Audit deliverable?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Written, prioritized roadmap covering current state, recommended workflows, platform recommendation, 90-day plan, budget estimate. 1-3 weeks.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you compete with larger consultancies on Bay Area engagements?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Sometimes. We're typically faster and more execution-focused; larger firms typically have more analytical depth and more layers.</p></div>
</div></section>

